# pnpm workspace config.
#
# Why public-hoist the React type packages:
# @react-three/fiber ships a TypeScript augmentation (declare module 'react' /
# 'react/jsx-runtime') that adds every three.js element (<mesh>, <group>,
# <points>, ...) to JSX.IntrinsicElements. For that augmentation to BIND, tsc
# must be able to resolve @types/react by walking up from fiber's location deep
# inside pnpm's isolated store. In a single-project layout @types/react sat in
# the root node_modules and was reachable; once the app moved under /web (its
# deps with it), pnpm's strict, isolated node_modules no longer exposes
# @types/react at a level fiber can see, so the augmentation silently fails and
# all R3F JSX elements disappear from the type checker.
#
# Public-hoisting just the React type packages restores a reachable
# @types/react at the workspace-root node_modules, reproducing the pre-monorepo
# resolution without loosening isolation for anything else. (Introduced with the
# ADR-004 monorepo migration.)
public-hoist-pattern[]=@types/react
public-hoist-pattern[]=@types/react-dom
